-- OTP Bank Rises as Hungarian Stocks Rally After Four-Day Weekend
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-03-19T08:27:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/otp-bank-rises-as-hungarian-stocks-rally-after-four-day-weekend.html
OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP) ,  Hungary ’s largest
lender, headed for the biggest gain in more than a week as the
country’s stocks rallied after a four-day holiday.  The shares rose 2.8 percent to 4,020 forint by 9:12 a.m. in
Budapest. The benchmark BUX stock  index  advanced 0.5 percent to
19,474.04. The Budapest Stock Exchange was closed on March 15
and March 16 when European equities rose to an eight-month high.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
